- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method utilizes attention mechanism and message-passing relay, which are commonly used in AI research. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper proposes a new method for topic-specific sentiment analysis based on node classification and text classification, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method can be applied to graph classification and link prediction tasks, which are commonly used in computer vision and pattern recognition. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The proposed method is specifically designed for graph data, which falls under the domain of social and information networks.
